quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  16,15,"And He has placed into the earth firm mountains, so it does not tremor with you, and there are rivers and pathways so that you may find your way"
  16,16,and landmarks and the stars by which they find their way
  16,17,Is then He Who creates equal to one who cannot create? Will you not then take heed
  16,18,"If you try to count Allah’s favors, you will not be able to enumerate them. Indeed, Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  16,19,Allah knows all that you conceal and all that you reveal
  16,20,"But those whom they invoke besides Allah do not create anything, rather, they themselves are created"
  16,21,"They are dead, not living; not even knowing when they will be resurrected"
  16,22,"Your God is One God. But those who do not believe in the Hereafter, their hearts refuse to know, and they are arrogant"
  16,23,"Undoubtedly, Allah knows what they conceal and what they reveal. Indeed, He does not like those who are arrogant"
  16,24,"When it is said to them, “What has your Lord sent down?” They say, “Ancient fables!”"
  16,25,They will bear their burdens in full on the Day of Resurrection and some burdens of those whom they misled without knowledge. How terrible is what they will bear
  16,26,"Those who came before them plotted, so Allah uprooted their buildings from their foundations and the roof fell down on top of them, and the punishment came on them from where they could not imagine"